He concluded that, “other than the divorce statistics, my study shows that our community, especially Kuwaiti community minds, are coming to the conclusion and coming to a position that they’ll just ignore incest and they’ll stay quiet about this one because they see it somehow as a violation of the privacy rights of the offender victimizing something that has no impact on the security of our community, our country. Thus, rather than saying that those couple of people who dared to speak outside how it works, to teach the public that such terrible sin should not be kept secret, is the thing that is right and it’s the thing that should be practiced.”
Daniel Martínez Medrano Tafolla, Conflict Resolution Scholar Practitioner, Latin American Community of Norway (LACONRO)
Daniel Martínez Medrano Tafolla studied International Development, “Analytical Conflict Transformation” at NITO/AUC and Conflict Resolution and Mediation at Centro de Investigaciones Lagos, Universidad de las Américas Puebla, Mexico and Caja Judicial and Coimbra Universidade de Coimebra, Portugal and other private organizations with Conflict Resolution Departments. He obtained the diploma “International peace building and peace keeping” from the Northern Foreign Affairs College in Kiev, Ukraina. He obtained a Diploma in Knowledge Society Development as Project adapted from Stockholm Principle in the Urban Center. He also holds a licentiate degree in Criminal Administration.
Daniel Mart
